Cookies: 
"In a .NET API, I implement cookies using the HttpContext.Response.Cookies.Append method to set cookies, and HttpContext.Request.Cookies to read them. I typically use persistent, secure, and HttpOnly cookies to store non-sensitive session-related data or tokens.

For example, I might store a session ID or a CSRF token in a cookie like this:

HttpContext.Response.Cookies.Append("SessionId", sessionId, new CookieOptions
{
    HttpOnly = true,
    Secure = true,
    SameSite = SameSiteMode.Strict,
    Expires = DateTimeOffset.UtcNow.AddDays(7)
});
